<!-- Instruction -->
<div class="w3-container" id="instruction">
  <h1 class="w3-border-light-grey w3-padding-16">instructions for contributors</h1>
	<p>Our aim is to introduce representative snippets within the topics of interest. These snippets may present the core points of a phenomenon or an analysis with introducing the basic facts and point to further readings for a deeper understanding. In the following webpage, you find detailed instructions for the contents, the form and the technical issues of the video units:
	</p>
	<p><a href="instructions.html" class="w3-button w3-card-4 w3-grey">instructions for lecturers</a> 
	</p>
	<p>Course participants are invited to contribute with research posters. You find  instructions for posters and video-recorded oral presentations here:
	</p>
	<p><a href="instructionsStudents.html" class="w3-button w3-card-4 w3-grey">instructions for participants</a> 
	</p>
</div>

<!-- Films -->
<div class="w3-container" id="films">
  <h1 class="w3-border-light-grey w3-padding-16">films about Mayan people</h1>
  <ul class="w3-ul w3-card" style="width:80%">
  	<li><font color="blue"><a href="https://www.youtube.com/@cinejanal5650" target="_blank">Cine Janal</a></font>
		<br>YouTube channel with various films around the Yucatec Mayan culture and gastronomy. You may want to see <font color="blue"><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SufKukIZpsw" target="_blank">El Pib</a></font> with a child narration in Yucatec Maya, and Spanish/English/German subtitles.
		</li>
	<li><font color="blue"><a href="https://youtu.be/Jk-hO9y2v14?feature=shared" target="_blank">Who are the Mayans? documentary</a></font>
		<br> by Alice Chapman: pictures from Mayan people and culture in Guatemala [13 min.].
		</li>
	<li><font color="blue"><a href="https://youtu.be/V-isuWCXlbk?feature=shared" target="_blank">Discover Humanity: Guatemala</a></font>
		<br>by the Humanity project: about the culture and the current way of living in Guatemala, with many contributions of Mayan people [15 min.].
		</li>
	<li><font color="blue"><a href="https://terralingua.org/langscape_articles/to-the-roots-a-maya-reunion/" target="_blank">To the Roots: A Maya Reunion</a></font>
		<br>by Steve Bartz, 1998: interviews with Itzá and Lancadon Maya, discussions about the culture and the relation to the nature [27 min.].
		</li>
	<li><font color="blue"><a href="https://youtu.be/1mkyICN8dyM?feature=shared" target="_blank">Connecting with the Lacandon maya tribe | Tropicfeel Presents: Thousand Unspoken Words, with Chema Balbuena</a></font>
		<br>by Tropicfeel: short film with impressive pictures of landscapes and short introduction of the Lacandon people (by a photographer) [2 min.].
		</li>
		
</ul>

</div>

